{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Analyse Factorielle des Correspondances (AFC)\n",
    "## Élections Présidentielles France 2012\n",
    "### Premier tour\n",
    "\n",
    "**Étudiant:** [Votre Nom]\n",
    "\n",
    "**Objectif:** Analyser la structure des votes aux élections présidentielles 2012 selon les régions et les candidats, en testant l'indépendance entre ces deux variables qualitatives.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Importation des bibliothèques et données"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configuration pour les graphiques\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-darkgrid')\n",
    "sns.set_palette('husl')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Charger les données\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('ADEM_YENGUI_-_resultats_presidentielles_2012.csv')\n",
    "print(\"Données chargées:\")\n",
    "print(df.head())\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDimensions: {df.shape[0]} régions × {df.shape[1]-1} candidats\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Analyse Descriptive du Tableau de Contingence"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Définir les régions comme index\n",
    "df_contingence = df.set_index('Region')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Effectifs totaux\n",
    "N = df_contingence.values.sum()  # Effectif total\n",
    "n_i = df_contingence.sum(axis=1)  # Effectifs par ligne (régions)\n",
    "n_j = df_contingence.sum(axis=0)  # Effectifs par colonne (candidats)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"TABLEAU DE CONTINGENCE - EFFECTIFS CONJOINTS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(df_contingence)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nEffectif total N = {N:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nEffectifs marginaux des lignes (régions):\")\n",
    "print(n_i)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nEffectifs marginaux des colonnes (candidats):\")\n",
    "print(n_j)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Matrice des Fréquences\n",
    "\n",
    "Les fréquences sont calculées par: $f_{ij} = \\frac{n_{ij}}{N}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Matrice des fréquences\n",
    "F = df_contingence / N\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"MATRICE DES FRÉQUENCES (f_ij)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(F.round(4))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSomme totale: {F.sum().sum():.6f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Profils Lignes et Colonnes\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4.1 Profils Lignes\n",
    "Les profils lignes sont: $f_{i|j} = \\frac{f_{ij}}{f_{i.}} = \\frac{n_{ij}}{n_{i.}}$\n",
    "\n",
    "Ils représentent la distribution des votes pour chaque région."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Profils lignes: distribution du vote par région\n",
    "f_i_dot = F.sum(axis=1)  # Profil moyen des lignes\n",
    "profils_lignes = F.div(f_i_dot, axis=0)  # Diviser chaque ligne par son total\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"PROFILS LIGNES (Répartition des votes par région)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(profils_lignes.round(4))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nProfil moyen des lignes (f_i.):\")\n",
    "print(f_i_dot.round(4))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nVérification - Somme de chaque profil ligne = 1:\")\n",
    "print(profils_lignes.sum(axis=1).round(4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.2 Profils Colonnes\n",
    "Les profils colonnes sont: $f_{j|i} = \\frac{f_{ij}}{f_{.j}} = \\frac{n_{ij}}{n_{.j}}$\n",
    "\n",
    "Ils représentent la répartition géographique du vote pour chaque candidat."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Profils colonnes: répartition géographique par candidat\n",
    "f_dot_j = F.sum(axis=0)  # Profil moyen des colonnes\n",
    "profils_colonnes = F.div(f_dot_j, axis=1)  # Diviser chaque colonne par son total\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"PROFILS COLONNES (Répartition régionale par candidat)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(profils_colonnes.round(4))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nProfil moyen des colonnes (f_.j):\")\n",
    "print(f_dot_j.round(4))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nVérification - Somme de chaque profil colonne = 1:\")\n",
    "print(profils_colonnes.sum(axis=0).round(4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Test d'Indépendance - Chi-Deux\n",
    "\n",
    "**Hypothèse nulle (H₀):** Les deux variables sont indépendantes\n",
    "**Hypothèse alternative (H₁):** Les deux variables sont dépendantes\n",
    "\n",
    "La statistique du Chi-deux est: $\\chi^2 = N \\sum_{i,j} \\frac{(f_{ij} - f_{i.} f_{.j})^2}{f_{i.} f_{.j}}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test du Chi-Deux\n",
    "# Fréquences théoriques sous indépendance\n",
    "f_theo = np.outer(f_i_dot, f_dot_j)\n",
    "n_theo = f_theo * N\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calcul de la statistique Chi-Deux\n",
    "chi2_stat = N * ((F - f_theo)**2 / f_theo).sum().sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Degrés de liberté\n",
    "ddl = (df_contingence.shape[0] - 1) * (df_contingence.shape[1] - 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# p-value\n",
    "p_value = 1 - stats.chi2.cdf(chi2_stat, ddl)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Valeur critique à 5%\n",
    "chi2_critique = stats.chi2.ppf(0.95, ddl)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"TEST D'INDÉPENDANCE - CHI-DEUX\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(f\"Statistique Chi-Deux: χ² = {chi2_stat:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Degrés de liberté: {ddl}\")\n",
    "print(f\"p-value: {p_value:.2e}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Seuil critique (α=5%): χ²_{0.95},{ddl} = {chi2_critique:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\n{'='*80}\")\n",
    "if chi2_stat > chi2_critique:\n",
    "    print(\"✓ CONCLUSION: On REJETTE l'hypothèse d'indépendance (p < 0.05)\")\n",
    "    print(\"  Les régions et les candidats ne sont PAS indépendants.\")\n",
    "    print(\"  Il existe une ASSOCIATION SIGNIFICATIVE entre les deux variables.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"✗ CONCLUSION: On NE REJETTE PAS l'hypothèse d'indépendance\")\n",
    "    print(\"  Les régions et les candidats sont indépendants.\")\n",
    "print(f\"{'='*80}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Matrice des Taux de Liaison (Phi-2)\n",
    "\n",
    "Le taux de liaison mesure le degré d'association entre deux modalités:\n",
    "$$t_{ij} = \\frac{f_{ij} - f_{i.}f_{.j}}{f_{i.}f_{.j}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- Valeur positive: association positive (surreprésentation)\n",
    "- Valeur négative: association négative (sous-représentation)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Taux de liaison\n",
    "t_ij = (F - f_theo) / f_theo\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"MATRICE DES TAUX DE LIAISON\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(t_ij.round(4))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nValeur minimale: {t_ij.min().min():.4f} (Sous-représentation maximale)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Valeur maximale: {t_ij.max().max():.4f} (Surreprésentation maximale)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Identifier les associations principales\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"PRINCIPALES ASSOCIATIONS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"\\nTop 10 des associations POSITIVES (surreprésentation):\")\n",
    "t_flat = t_ij.stack().sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "for idx, val in enumerate(t_flat.head(10), 1):\n",
    "    region, candidat = t_flat.index[idx-1]\n",
    "    print(f\"{idx}. {region:25s} - {candidat:15s}: {val:7.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nTop 10 des associations NÉGATIVES (sous-représentation):\")\n",
    "for idx, val in enumerate(t_flat.tail(10), 1):\n",
    "    region, candidat = t_flat.index[-(11-idx)]\n",
    "    print(f\"{idx}. {region:25s} - {candidat:15s}: {val:7.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Inertie et Distances\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.1 Inertie Totale\n",
    "\n",
    "L'inertie totale mesure l'écart à l'indépendance:\n",
    "$$\\Phi^2 = \\sum_{i,j} f_{i.} f_{.j} t_{ij}^2 = \\frac{\\chi^2}{N}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Inertie totale\n",
    "inertie_totale = (f_i_dot.values[:, np.newaxis] * f_dot_j.values[np.newaxis, :] * t_ij**2).sum().sum()\n",
    "inertie_totale_chi2 = chi2_stat / N\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"INERTIE TOTALE\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(f\"Inertie totale (Φ²) = {inertie_totale:.6f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Vérification (χ²/N) = {inertie_totale_chi2:.6f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nChî-deux: χ² = N × Φ² = {chi2_stat:.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 7.2 Distance du Phi-Carré\n",
    "\n",
    "La distance du Phi-carré (métrique de Riemannian) entre deux profils lignes i et i' est:\n",
    "$$d_\\Phi^2(L_i, L_{i'}) = \\sum_j \\frac{(f_{i|j} - f_{i'|j})^2}{f_{.j}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Cette distance a la propriété d'**équivalence distributionnelle**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Matrice de distance Phi-carré entre régions\n",
    "def distance_phi2_lignes(profils, f_dot_j):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calcule la distance Phi-carré entre les profils lignes\"\"\"\n",
    "    n_regions = profils.shape[0]\n",
    "    dist_matrix = np.zeros((n_regions, n_regions))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(n_regions):\n",
    "        for i_prime in range(i, n_regions):\n",
    "            if i == i_prime:\n",
    "                dist_matrix[i, i_prime] = 0\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                diff = (profils.iloc[i] - profils.iloc[i_prime])**2\n",
    "                dist = (diff / f_dot_j).sum()\n",
    "                dist_matrix[i, i_prime] = np.sqrt(dist)\n",
    "                dist_matrix[i_prime, i] = np.sqrt(dist)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return dist_matrix\n",
    "\n",
    "# Distance Phi-carré\n",
    "dist_phi2_lignes = distance_phi2_lignes(profils_lignes, f_dot_j)\n",
    "dist_phi2_lignes_df = pd.DataFrame(dist_phi2_lignes, \n",
    "                                    index=profils_lignes.index,\n",
    "                                    columns=profils_lignes.index)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"MATRICE DE DISTANCE PHI-CARRÉ (Régions)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(dist_phi2_lignes_df.round(4).iloc[:10, :10])  # Afficher une sous-matrice\n",
    "print(\"\\n(Matrice complète disponible en variable dist_phi2_lignes_df)\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDistance moyenne: {dist_phi2_lignes[np.triu_indices_from(dist_phi2_lignes, k=1)].mean():.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Décomposition en Valeurs Propres (AFC proprement dite)\n",
    "\n",
    "On utilise la décomposition en valeurs propres de la matrice de variance-covariance des taux de liaison."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Centrer et normaliser pour l'AFC\n",
    "# Matrice à analyser: taux de liaison pondérés\n",
    "# X = sqrt(f_i.) * sqrt(f_.j) * t_ij\n",
    "\n",
    "sqrt_fi = np.sqrt(f_i_dot.values)\n",
    "sqrt_fj = np.sqrt(f_dot_j.values)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Matrice centrée et pondérée\n",
    "X_afc = t_ij.values  # Déjà centré (contient les écarts à l'indépendance)\n",
    "X_weighted = (sqrt_fi[:, np.newaxis] * sqrt_fj[np.newaxis, :]) * t_ij.values\n",
    "\n",
    "# SVD de la matrice\n",
    "U, Sigma, Vt = np.linalg.svd(X_weighted, full_matrices=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Valeurs propres et inertie\n",
    "eigenvalues = Sigma**2\n",
    "inertie_relative = eigenvalues / eigenvalues.sum()\n",
    "inertie_cumulative = np.cumsum(inertie_relative)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"VALEURS PROPRES ET INERTIES\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "results_eigenvalues = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Axe': np.arange(1, len(eigenvalues) + 1),\n",
    "    'Valeur Propre': eigenvalues,\n",
    "    'Valeur Prop. Relative (%)': inertie_relative * 100,\n",
    "    'Inertie Cumulative (%)': inertie_cumulative * 100,\n",
    "    'Chi²': eigenvalues * N\n",
    "})\n",
    "print(results_eigenvalues.to_string(index=False))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nInertie totale (Φ²) = {eigenvalues.sum():.6f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nNote: Les 2-3 premiers axes représentent généralement 80-90% de l'inertie.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Coordonnées Factorielles\n",
    "\n",
    "### 9.1 Coordonnées des individus-lignes (Régions)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Coordonnées factorielles des lignes\n",
    "# Ψ_ik = U_ik / sqrt(f_i.)\n",
    "n_axes = min(4, len(eigenvalues))  # Garder les 4 premiers axes\n",
    "\n",
    "psi = U[:, :n_axes] / sqrt_fi[:, np.newaxis]\n",
    "coord_lignes = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    psi,\n",
    "    index=profils_lignes.index,\n",
    "    columns=[f'Axe {i+1}' for i in range(n_axes)]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"COORDONNÉES FACTORIELLES DES RÉGIONS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(coord_lignes.round(4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 9.2 Coordonnées des individus-colonnes (Candidats)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"text/plain": ""}
  },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Coordonnées factorielles des colonnes\n",
    "# Φ_jk = V_jk / sqrt(f_.j)\n",
    "phi = Vt[:n_axes, :].T / sqrt_fj[np.newaxis, :]\n",
    "coord_colonnes = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    phi,\n",
    "    index=profils_colonnes.index,\n",
    "    columns=[f'Axe {i+1}' for i in range(n_axes)]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"COORDONNÉES FACTORIELLES DES CANDIDATS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(coord_colonnes.round(4))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Qualité de Représentation et Contributions\n",
    "\n",
    "### 10.1 Contributions des régions à l'inertie"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Contributions absolues des lignes à l'inertie de chaque axe\n",
    "# Ctr(i, k) = (f_i. * Ψ_ik²) / λ_k\n",
    "\n",
    "contrib_lignes = np.zeros((len(profils_lignes), n_axes))\n",
    "for k in range(n_axes):\n",
    "    contrib_lignes[:, k] = (f_i_dot.values * psi[:, k]**2) / eigenvalues[k] * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "contrib_lignes_df = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    contrib_lignes,\n",
    "    index=profils_lignes.index,\n",
    "    columns=[f'Axe {i+1}' for i in range(n_axes)]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"CONTRIBUTIONS DES RÉGIONS À L'INERTIE (%)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "contrib_lignes_display = contrib_lignes_df.copy()\n",
    "contrib_lignes_display['Total'] = contrib_lignes_display.sum(axis=1)\n",
    "print(contrib_lignes_display.round(2))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSomme par axe (doit être 100%):\")\n",
    "print(contrib_lignes_df.sum().round(2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 10.2 Contributions des candidats à l'inertie"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Contributions absolues des colonnes à l'inertie de chaque axe\n",
    "# Ctr(j, k) = (f_.j * Φ_jk²) / λ_k\n",
    "\n",
    "contrib_colonnes = np.zeros((len(profils_colonnes), n_axes))\n",
    "for k in range(n_axes):\n",
    "    contrib_colonnes[:, k] = (f_dot_j.values * phi[:, k]**2) / eigenvalues[k] * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "contrib_colonnes_df = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    contrib_colonnes,\n",
    "    index=profils_colonnes.index,\n",
    "    columns=[f'Axe {i+1}' for i in range(n_axes)]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "print(\"CONTRIBUTIONS DES CANDIDATS À L'INERTIE (%)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*80)\n",
    "contrib_colonnes_display = contrib_colonnes_df.copy()\n",
    "contrib_colonnes_display['Total'] = contrib_colonnes_display.sum(axis=1)\n",
    "print(contrib_colonnes_display.round(2))\n",
    "print(f\"\\nSomme par axe (doit être 100%):\")\n",
    "print(contrib_colonnes_df.sum().round(2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 10.3 Qualité de Représentation (Cosinus Carrés)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"text/plain": ""}
  },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Cosinus carrés (QLT) - Qualité de représentation sur chaque axe\n",
    "# Pour les lignes: QLT(i,k) = Ψ_ik² / d²_Φ(i, origine)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Distance au centre pour les lignes\n",
    "dist2_lignes = (psi**2).sum(axis=1)\n",
    "cos2_lignes = np.zeros((len(profils_lignes), n_axes))\n",
    "for k in range(n_axes):\n",
    "    cos2_lignes[:, k] = psi[:, k]**2 / dist2_lignes * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "cos2_lignes_df = pd.DataFrame(\n",
